<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881025-0139 </DOCNO><HL> Enterprise: Silvar-Lisco Is Considering Company's Sale or Merger </HL><SO> </SO><CO> SVRL </CO><IN> TNM </IN><DATELINE> MENLO PARK, Calif.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Silvar-Lisco said it is considering the possible sale or merger of the company. The maker of computer-aided engineering software products said it retained Alex. Brown andamp; Sons Inc. to advise its directors on alternatives to &quot;maximize shareholder value.&quot;    The company has said it expects to post a loss of $1.5 million to $2 million for the second quarter ended Sept. 30, compared with a loss of $814,000 on revenue of $6.1 million a year earlier. The company also said it would dismiss 10% to 15% of its 200 employees and cut expenses.    Silvar-Lisco closed yesterday in national over-the-counter trading at $2.125 a share, up 25 cents. </TEXT></DOC>